cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a novel two-phase transmission protocol for UAV swarm communication in a cellular network, which involves exploiting device-to-device (D2D) communication. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper aims to characterize the reliability performance of the proposed protocol, which involves analyzing the expected percentage of UAVs in the swarm that can decode the common control message. This falls under the scope of information theory.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a protocol for controlling and communicating with a UAV swarm, which involves multiple ground base stations and D2D communication. This falls under the scope of systems and control.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of D2D communication for relaying a common control message among UAVs in the swarm, which can involve multimedia data transmission. This falls under the scope of multimedia.
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses the communication and control of a UAV swarm, which falls under the scope of robotics.
